he "functional principle," and the difficulties inherent in Canada's role in the diplomacy of the post-World War II era. In keeping with the immediacy of Granatstein's concerns is John Erickson's lucid presentation of Soviet military philosophy, a matter of crucial and immediate concern. This book will be of interest to military historians, political scientists, and the more general reader intrigued by military history and philosophy. These essays, edited and compiled by Keith Neilson and Roy Prete, who teach in the Department of History at the Royal Military College, Kingston, were presented at the Eighth Royal Military College Military History Symposium.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCombined operations (Military science)xHistoryvCongresses. 4aHistory: Military History. 4aPolitical Science: International Relations. 7aHISTORY / Modern / 20th Century.2bisacsh1 aErickson, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGranatstein, J. L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKennedy, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNeilson, Keith, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aNish, Ian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStone, Norman, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTrumpener, Ulrich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.51644/978088920672440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780889206724423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780889206724/original  a978-3-11-